    • Method Detail

      • taskFinished

        @HTTPServiceMethod(name="taskFinished",
                   acceptedMethods="POST")
public void taskFinished(@HTTPMethodParameter(name="body",bodyParameter=true)
                                                                                                              InputStreamParameter xml)
        The request is to be sent in the body of POST method. The Content-Type header MUST be set to "text/xml". The character set MUST be UTF-8. For example, "Content-Type: text/xml; charset=UTF-8". The method can be called multiple times by the back-ends. Each call is assumed to be an incremental update on the previous one and can contain any amount of new information. It is also possible to update previously submitted data by using the same identifiers: video GUID (for videos), and media object id or a combination of back-end id and object id (for media objects). Task results may contain video specific back-end status information, though it is not required. Using an invalid back-end id (both for the task and the generated media objects) can result in an error, causing the entire task result to be rejected. It is not allowed for a one back-end to update/modify media objects previously submitted by another back-end, or by the user.

        Example Query:

        POST /rest/vcars/taskFinished
        Content-Type: text/xml; charset=UTF-8

        @HTTPServiceMethod(name="queryTaskDetails",
